After taking this course, students should:
• Critically understand key concepts related to intimate relationships, such as love, marriage, and family;
• Grasp the main issues of family and marriage in the Chinese context;
• Apply a theoretical debate on the social and cultural construction of one’s “private” versus “public” life and their
historical significance;
• Learn ethnographic methods to collect data on people’s everyday intimate experiences;
• Develop oral skills to present coherent and succinct analysis;
• Be able to locate and use secondary sources relevant to selected topics.

