Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:

1) gain a better understanding of the evolution and development of the Chinese economy since the 1980s;

2) identify the scope, nature, value and limitations of a market and a planned economy;

3) understand how the evolution of economic institutions is closely related to social, political, historical forces;

4) critically evaluate major achievements and considerable problems in China’s business and economy.

Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:
1) understand the historical process of housing privatisation in Mainland China since 1979;
2) grasp how transformations in the housing sector have triggered other changes in urban livelihood;
3) critically analyse current housing and urban governance issues in China.

